An Act authorizing pharmacists to provide opioid use disorder treatment.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 32A of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
2 section 17W the following section:-
3 Section 17X. (a) The commission shall provide to any active or retired employee of the
4 commonwealth who is insured under the group insurance commission coverage for collaborative
5 drug therapy, as defined by section 24B½ of chapter 112, performed by a pharmacist at a rate not
6 less than that provided to other nonphysician practitioners if the therapy:
7 (i) is for the treatment of opioid use disorder;
8 (ii) is within the scope of practice of the pharmacist; and
9 (iii) would otherwise be covered if the service or procedure were provided by any health
10 care service provider or practitioner, including a physician, advance practice registered nurse or
11 physician assistant.
